## Ongoing Operations

**To check if stream is running:**
SSH into VPS → `tmux attach -t stream` → FFmpeg output should be scrolling with incrementing `time=`

**If stream has stopped (e.g. VPS rebooted):**
```
ssh root@138.197.9.139
tmux new -s stream
ffmpeg -re -stream_loop -1 -i HoldtLoop.mp4 -c:v copy -c:a copy -f flv rtmp://live.restream.io/live/re_10860387_75ea120b5509c4a2572f
```

**When going live from OBS (writing/gaming stream):**
1. SSH into VPS → tmux attach → press `Q` to stop FFmpeg
2. Start OBS stream to Restream as normal
3. When done live streaming, SSH back in and restart FFmpeg command above

**If Restream stream key ever changes:**
Update the RTMP URL at the end of the FFmpeg command with the new key from Restream dashboard → Settings → RTMP.

**To update the file on the VPS (e.g. new animation from Marwan):**
1. Build new `HoldtLoop.mp4` locally using same FFmpeg process
2. Stop FFmpeg on VPS
3. `scp D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 root@138.197.9.139:/root/`
4. Restart FFmpeg
